<h2><strong>Transcript</strong></h2>
<p>[<em>Theme plays</em>]</p>
<p><strong>STEVE STROGATZ:</strong> This is “The Joy of Why.” I’m Steve Strogatz.</p>
<p><strong>JANNA LEVIN:</strong> And I’m Janna Levin.</p>
<p><strong>STROGATZ:</strong> And here we are together. It’s a little different wrinkle for us. Last season, we took turns at the microphone interviewing guests from all different walks of science and math; now we’re some kind of team.</p>
<p><strong>LEVIN: </strong>We’re going to sit down together more. We’re going to interview big scientists about big ideas.</p>
<p><strong>STROGATZ:</strong> I’m really looking forward to it because, first of all, it’s fun to work with you. You can always learn a lot from your friends. But what do you think is being brought to the table by having us do this together?</p>
</div>
        </div>
    </div>
